{{for|the village in [[Bistrița-Năsăud County]]|Nimigea}} {{Infobox prepared food | name = Mititei | image = Mititei aufm Grill.jpg | image_size = 260px | imagesize = 220px | caption = Mititei on the grill. | alternate_name = Mici Romania | region = | creator = | course = [[Main course]] | served = Hot | main_ingredient = [[Lamb and mutton|Lamb]], [[pork]], [[beef]], [[coriander]], [[onion]], [[garlic]], [[black pepper]], [[thyme]], [[Sodium bicarbonate#Cooking|sodium bicarbonate]] | variations = | calories = | other = }}
'''Mititei''' ({{IPA-ro|mitiˈtej}}) or '''mici''' ({{IPA-ro|mit͡ʃʲ|pron}}, both Romanian words meaning "small ones") is a traditional [[Romanian cuisine|Romanian]] dish of grilled [[ground meat]] rolls made from a mixture of [[beef]], [[Lamb and mutton|lamb]] and [[pork]] with [[spice]]s, such as [[garlic]], [[black pepper]], [[thyme]], [[coriander]], [[anise]], [[Savory (herb)|savory]], and sometimes a touch of [[paprika]]. [[Sodium bicarbonate#Cooking|Sodium bicarbonate]] and [[broth]] or water are also added to the mixture. It is similar to [[ćevapi]].<ref name="Ceva Bun 2009">{{Cite web |url=http://www.cevabun.ro/mititeii-de-la-carul-cu-bere-povestea-reteta-proba/ |title=Reteta originala de mititei de la Caru cu Bere |date=21 May 2009 |website=Ceva Bun |language=Romanian |access-date=2018-01-14}}</ref>
It is often served with [[french fries]], [[Mustard (condiment)|mustard]] and ''[[murături]]'' (Romanian pickled vegetables).
